author: Don Thrasher
title: Touch talks about D.C., Sweetest Day (Rock Insider)
text:
​Local R&B group Touch, presenting its annual Sweetest Day Show at Gilly’s on Saturday, Oct. 17, has received a boost in out-of-town bookings since placing third on NBC’s “The Winner Is” in 2013.
However, a gig in Washington, D.C., last month came from an old classmate from Roth High School. Dayton native Joyce Beatty, the U.S. Representative for Ohio’s 3rd congressional district, invited the group to perform during Congressional Black Caucus Week.
Continue reading on MyDaytonDailyNews.com. »
